1. Vitalik: Ethereum needs a large number of young people with cypherpunk visions;
2. ZachXBT: An unknown victim was attacked by North Korean hacker Lazarus Group on Tron and lost about $3.1 million;
3. Metis launched a new high-performance chain Hyperion dedicated to AI, which will launch a test network before April this year;
4. CZ mentioned the idea of ​​a new token issuance mechanism: 10% will be unlocked initially, and certain price conditions must be met before further unlocking;
5. Danny Ryan will join Etherealize as a co-founder, and Vitalik expressed "welcome to return";
6. Vitalik: Fusaka upgrades will also need to be performed in 2025, and it is hoped that the relevant test network will be launched the day after Pectra is upgraded;
7. Trump will host the first White House Cryptocurrency Summit on March 7;
8. The President of the Swiss National Bank said that Bitcoin is not suitable as a reserve asset;
9. The US spot Bitcoin ETF ended 8 consecutive days of net outflows and recorded net inflows for the first time;
10. Mask Network founder Suji Yan Issued an ultimatum to hackers;

11. NFT transaction volume fell 28.93% month-on-month to US$107.1 million in the past 7 days.
